%div#home_div
  %div#home_left_col
    %p
      %b Proteopathogen2.0, a database and web tool to store and display Proteomics Identification Results in the MzIdentML standard format
    %p 
      Proteopathogen2.0 is a database-backed web application on shotgun Proteomics experiments addressed at
      the study of <i>Candida albicans</i> and other fungal pathogens and their interaction with the host.  
      It follows the idea first implemented in the original version of Proteopathogen, 
      =link_to 'proteopathogen.dacya.ucm.es', 'http://proteopathogen.dacya.ucm.es'
      =link_to '(Vialas 2009, Proteomics)', 'http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19743419'
    %p
      It stores peptide and protein identification results in a database that directly maps elements from 
      =link_to 'the mzIdentML standard', 'http://www.psidev.info/mzidentml', target: 'blank'
      , the HUPO-Proteomics Standard Initiative adopted "exchange format for peptides and proteins identified from mass spectra".
    
      The data consists of high confidence peptide and protein identifications coming from the
      =link_to 'Candida albicans PeptideAtlas',  'https://db.systemsbiology.net/sbeams/cgi/PeptideAtlas/buildDetails?atlas_build_id=323'
      =link_to '(Vialas 2014, Journal of Proteomics)', 'http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23811049'
      but Proteopathogen2.0 welcomes identification results in the MzIdentML format from experiments
      related to fungal pathogen proteomics.      

    = image_tag  "mzidentml.png"

